"Abstract What would you do if you were stuck in one place, and every day was exactly the same, and nothing you did mattered?” Phil Connor, Ground Hog Day “That about sums it up for me,” answered Ralph, and I’m sure most system administrators, information system security officers (ISSOs), physical security, operations security, and other security professionals would agree. Everybody takes them for granted — until the network goes down or applications can’t be used. And that’s the problem: a totally wrong perception of what’s required for the serious business of properly doing full spectrum security. Security is not something extra. Security is a normal part of doing business."
